{"type":"message","id":"4eebfaee","parentId":"a1b5637d","timestamp":"2026-03-28T07:59:33.484Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The mainline guard shows ALERT. The state file shows the morning news was generated successfully yesterday (2026-03-27) but the mainline guard says `08:50晨报：MISSING | 最近成功：None`. Let me check the health report and the state file more carefully.\n\nWait - the state file shows `status: \"OK\"` and `last_success_at: \"2026-03-27 08:50:27\"`. But the mainline guard says MISSING. This is inconsistent. The mainline guard may be looking for today's (2026-03-28) morning news, but today is Saturday so there wouldn't be a morning news. \n\nI think the issue is that the guard is checking for 2026-03-28 files when the state file only has yesterday's data. Since today is Saturday, there shouldn't be morning news generated at all. The guard's warning seems to be flagging the absence of today's file as a missing dependency, but that's expected behavior on a non-trading day. I need to look at the actual health report to see what's really being flagged.","thinkingSignature":"7adb48df0fefcfc3eac1d6740a0af882d71f12aa0a7a21d283817ad03a5d8b99"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v3ly0xzlv78i_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/research/reports/investment_research_mainline_health_20260328.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":9552,"output":279,"cacheRead":23128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32959,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774684763734,"responseId":"0616bd5b482a58e23c070366b48bd8d2"}}
