{"type":"message","id":"1f32aa31","parentId":"eaac6dbc","timestamp":"2026-03-28T07:59:43.660Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The health report is showing many \"normal\" items but marking them all as \"否\" (no). This seems like a logic bug in the health check script - it's saying \"normal\" but then marking as not generated. The \"缺口\" section also lists them as normal. This looks like a false alarm or a bug in the guard script. The state file shows yesterday's morning news was successfully generated and pushed. The health report seems to be incorrectly flagging this.\n\nToday is Saturday (non-trading day), so:\n- No morning news needed\n- No premarket precheck needed  \n- No live dashboard needed\n\nThe script seems to have a bug where it's not properly checking the \"normal\" items vs \"generated\" items. Let me check if the report's `缺口` (gaps) list makes sense - it lists them all as \"normal\" which contradicts the check items being \"否\".\n \nLooking at the actual exit code 20 with the overall status showing as \"告警\" (alert), there's a real issue here. The script is treating Saturday as if it should have trading data and flagging missing files as alerts, but the cron schedule only runs on weekdays. The core problem is that the health report has inconsistent logic - it's declaring items normal in one section while marking them as not generated in another, which suggests the guard script itself has a logic error in how it evaluates trading day versus non-trading day states.","thinkingSignature":"c05a45c38ea42567b3a46aa1850b41435f65c63a23b330253246b7c70c6bfdbf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mu2okmicikcl_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/run_investment_research_mainline_guard.py","limit":80}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":10175,"output":347,"cacheRead":23128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33650,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774684773567,"responseId":"0616bd652d66c80e7ba322b77a3406ba"}}
{"type":"message","id":"fa098b5b","parentId":"1f32aa31","timestamp":"2026-03-28T07:59:43.745Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mu2okmicikcl_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nWORKSPACE = Path.home() / \".openclaw\" / \"workspace\"\nREPORT_DIR = WORKSPACE / \"research\" / \"reports\"\nHEALTH_SCRIPT = WORKSPACE / \"scripts\" / \"generate_investment_research_mainline_health.py\"\n\n\ndef today_tag() -> str:\n    return datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d\")\n\n\ndef load_json(path: Path) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    return json.loads(path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n\n\ndef run_health() -> tuple[dict[str, Any], Path, Path]:\n    proc = subprocess.run([sys.executable, str(HEALTH_SCRIPT)], cwd=str(WORKSPACE), capture_output=True, text=True, check=True)\n    lines = [line.strip() for line in proc.stdout.splitlines() if line.strip()]\n    md_path = Path(lines[0]) if lines else REPORT_DIR / f\"investment_research_mainline_health_{today_tag()}.md\"\n    json_path = Path(lines[1]) if len(lines) > 1 else REPORT_DIR / f\"investment_research_mainline_health_{today_tag()}.json\"\n    payload = load_json(json_path)\n    return payload, md_path, json_path\n\n\ndef build_summary(payload: dict[str, Any], md_path: Path, json_path: Path) -> str:\n    base = payload.get(\"alert_message\") or \"🩺 量化投研主链巡检：UNKNOWN\"\n    return \"\\n\".join([\n        base,\n        f\"- 健康报告：`{md_path}`\",\n        f\"- 健康JSON：`{json_path}`\",\n    ])\n\n\ndef exit_code(overall: str) -> int:\n    if overall == \"OK\":\n        return 0\n    if overall == \"WARN\":\n        return 10\n    if overall == \"ALERT\":\n        return 20\n    return 30\n\n\ndef main() -> None:\n    payload, md_path, json_path = run_health()\n    print(build_summary(payload, md_path, json_path))\n    raise SystemExit(exit_code(payload.get(\"overall_status\", \"UNKNOWN\")))\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774684783735}}
{"type":"message","id":"c9135711","parentId":"fa098b5b","timestamp":"2026-03-28T07:59:53.277Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The guard script calls `generate_investment_research_mainline_health.py`. The ALERT comes from the health script itself. Let me check the health script to understand the logic, specifically around trading day vs non-trading day.\n\nActually, this is a known limitation. On non-trading days (Saturday), the health check flags many items as \"MISSING\" because the data from Friday (the last trading day) is still there but the system considers them stale. The real question is whether I need to report this as an alert or not.\n\nLooking at the HEARTBEAT.md rules:\n- \"非交易日且无异常\" → 保持安静\n\n\n- \"每日策略审计为 `ALERT`\" → 主动提醒\n\nSo the ALERT status from the quant ops health check should trigger a reminder, but I need to verify whether \"每日策略审计\" and \"量化投研主链巡检\" are the same thing or different checks. The daily strategy audit is a separate command from the mainline health check, so I should clarify if this ALERT is actually from the audit or from the health monitoring system.\n\nSince today is Saturday and non-trading, the premarket and live dashboard checks should stay quiet, but the daily strategy audit is still supposed to run daily. I need to check whether that audit script exists and what its actual output was.","thinkingSignature":"d1ad374f1b2628fbbbb04ff2adcd7afbf237d607bd2bd0694d98ff7bbf958470"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8c3eqiz6fxwm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace/quant_projects/personal-a-share-research-system && python3 scripts/run_daily_strategy_audit.py 2>&1 | tail -20","timeout":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11027,"output":353,"cacheRead":23128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34508,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","tim