{"type":"message","id":"c23552cf","parentId":"fe1cf936","timestamp":"2026-03-28T14:25:38.164Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error \"Feishu send does not support card with media\" must be coming from the OpenClaw core, not specifically from the Feishu extension files. Let me look at the OpenClaw core instead.\n\nActually, thinking about this differently - maybe I should try a completely different approach:\n\n1. Convert the docx to PDF and try to send that\n2. Use the `buffer` parameter with base64 encoded content directly\n3. Upload to a web-accessible URL and share the link\n4. Send as a text/card message with the full lyrics content\n\nFor option 4, the full lyrics are short enough to fit in a text message. Let me just read the lyrics file and send it as text.\n\n\nI could generate a PDF from the docx using python-docx, but that would require installing additional libraries. Let me focus on sending the content directly as a text message instead, though the user specifically requested a formatted document rather than plain text. The real issue seems to be that the OpenClaw message tool is adding a card parameter when filePath is provided, which Feishu's API doesn't support, so I need to find a way to send the file without triggering that card parameter.","thinkingSignature":"ef5a1bf3346fb802ecc9751e991605d1b8474a688326deed31648932bd5757af"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4b7wsxj8zopy_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /Users/ling/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.22.0/installation/lib/node_modules/openclaw -name \"*.js\" 2>/dev/null | xargs grep -l \"does not support card with media\" 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":18255,"output":332,"cacheRead":23128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41715,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774707929481,"respons