{"type":"message","id":"28b9adfd","parentId":"65c5ac79","timestamp":"2026-03-28T14:27:07.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so without a target, it tries to use the current conversation's channel, which is \"heartbeat\" - not a Feishu chat. That's expected.\n\nThe 400 error when sending to the user might be due to the Feishu app not having permission to send messages to that user, or the user ID being wrong, or the card format being wrong.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach - just send a plain text message without card, but since card is required, this won't work per the schema.\n\nActually, wait. The error says \"Request failed with status code 400\" for the card with proper content. This could be:\n1. The card JSON format is wrong for this Feishu app's card version\n\n\n2. The access token is invalid\n3. Some other API issue\n\nLet me check the Feishu app configuration or try to get more details about what a valid card looks like for this specific app. The `card` parameter seems to be passed directly to `runtime.sendCardFeishu()`, so I need to understand what format that function expects.\n\nI should also check if there's a `feishu_app_scopes` tool available to see what permissions are actually configured.","thinkingSignature":"2c2dbe2821cbffb9d9be577697617f3405e95e09ba5550d4440103ac4b020110"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_k02p9339d2k2_1","name":"feishu_app_scopes","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":23437,"output":269,"cacheRead":23128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46834,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774708019767,"responseId":"06171833c460d89027770dd99eb91c7f"}}
