{"type":"message","id":"fd675eb3","parentId":"233121b0","timestamp":"2026-03-28T14:27:42.935Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still 400. The issue might be that the Feishu bot's card format isn't compatible, or there's an API issue with sending to that specific user.\n\nLet me try sending a message without any card or media - just text. But the schema requires card. Wait, maybe if I send `card=null` or `card=false`?\n\nThe code says: `const card = ctx.params.card && typeof ctx.params.card === \"object\" ? ctx.params.card : void 0;`\nSo if card is `null` or `false`, it would be falsy and `card` would be `void 0` (undefined).\n\nBut the schema requires `card` as a required property... Let me check if passing `card: null` would satisfy the schema while also making the card undefined at runtime.\n\n\nThe schema validation probably runs before the runtime code, so passing `null` might still fail the schema check even though it would become `undefined` at runtime. Let me reconsider - the schema says `card: additionalProperties: true` with no `required` field, so it shouldn't actually be required at all, yet the error message says it must have the `card` property. That's odd since the schema itself doesn't list it as required.\n\nWait, looking at the actual schema definition more carefully - `card` is defined as an object with `additionalProperties: true` but no `required` array, so it shouldn't be mandatory. The validation error about `card` being required must be coming from somewhere else in the tool's parameter schema, not from this `card` field definition itself.\n\nLet me step back - I can't seem to fix the Feishu messaging issue right now, and I've spent enough time on it. The file exists and the user can access it directly. Since this is a heartbeat context rather than a direct Feishu DM, I should just report HEARTBEAT_OK and let the user know the file is ready.","thinkingSignature":"76afa0dc3f0e64487b0070dc82685d579272a9f59618e34dc05d73a4789f1d42"},{"type":"text","text":"Feishu message delivery has a technical blocker (400 error on card API). The docx file is confirmed ready at:\n`deliverables/lyrics/面向未来_去远航_打印版_20260328.docx`\n\n**Delivery issue summary:**\n- `message` tool requires `card` parameter per schema\n- Feishu API returns 400 when `card` is present (including empty `{}`)\n- `filePath` attachment requires `card` → always hits the card+media conflict\n- Card format attempts (`interactive`, `app` etc.) all return 400 — likely the Feishu bot's card configuration needs updating in the Feishu developer console\n\n**Status:** 文件已就绪，待 Feishu 消息通道修复后可重新推送。建议通过 workspace 直接访问 docx 文件。\n\nHEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":25070,"output":574,"cacheRead":23128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48772,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774708044477,"responseId":"0617184cb668ae9bc93d20b799caca6c"}}
